Docs.summary: Represents an individual schema within the Schema Library.

remarks.para: You can access the Schema Library from within Microsoft Word from the XML Schema tab in the Templates and Add-ins dialog box. The Schema Library represents schemas installed on a user's machine that a user has applied to a Word document or that a user has explicitly added to the Schema Library by using the Schema Library dialog box.

Use the property of the collection to return an individual XMLNameSpace object. The index value of the Item property can be either an Integer, which indicates the position of the schema in the Schema Library, or a String, which represents the name of the schema as returned using the property (the TargetNamespace setting defined in the schema).

Docs.summary: Returns a 32-bit integer that indicates the application in which the specified object was created.

remarks.para: If the object was created in Microsoft Word, this property returns the hexadecimal number 4D535744, which represents the string "MSWD." This value can also be represented by the constant wdCreatorCode.

The Creator property was primarily designed to be used on the Macintosh, where each application has a four-character creator code. For example, Microsoft Word has the creator code MSWD. For additional information about this property, consult the language reference Help included with Microsoft Office Macintosh Edition.
